Number of websites powered by Aspen: <span style="font-weight: bold;">1</span>.<br /><br /><a href="http://tech2.whit537.org/">tech2.whit537.org</a> serves some support files for this blog, and is an example of Aspen's auto-generated directory index. A modest beginning, to be sure. But it definitely confirms for me that <a href="http://www.zetadev.com/software/aspen/0.6/doc/html/command-line.html">Aspen's <span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">CLI</span></a> is well-designed: it's like a non-monolithic (<span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_1">microlithic</span>?) <span style="font-style: italic;"><span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_2">apachectl</span></span>, or a non-<span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_3">Zope</span>-specific <span style="font-style: italic;"><span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_4">zopectl</span></span>.<br /><br />I'm also upgrading a "real" website (~2k <span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_5">pageviews</span> per day) to Aspen, from a <span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_6">proto</span>-version of Aspen called <span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_7">httpyd</span>. I'm hoping to roll that out next week. Granted, it's not a migration from an entirely different system, but it does confirm for me that Aspen <a href="http://www.zetadev.com/software/aspen/0.6/doc/html/extending.html">has evolved in the right direction</a>.<br /><br />These <span onclick="BLOG_clickHandler(this)" class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_8">exercises</span> are <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=53">flushing</a> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=56">out</a> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=57">a</a> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=58">number</a> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=59">of</a> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=60">little</a> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/aspen/issues/detail?id=61">bugs</a>, which I'm hoping to fix in Aspen 0.7, to be released with that site roll-out.<div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/36506138-7599812544488825099?l=blag.whit537.org' alt='' /></div>
